gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Spurs 122, Nets 115
gameRecap.excerpt: San Antonio defeats Brooklyn, 122-115. For San Antonio, Victor Wembanyama had the game-saving block and led the way with 33 points, 16 rebounds, seven assists, and seven blocks while aided by Devin Vassell (25 points, eight assists) in the victory. Cam Thomas finished with 31 points, five assists, and two steals with Dennis Schroder adding 19 points and seven assists for Brooklyn in the losing effort. San Antonio improves to 15-53, while Brooklyn moves to 26-42 in the loss.
